title: Apple Logic Pro X 10.0.2
description:
Apple Logic Pro X 10.0.2


Logic Pro X introduces an advanced yet intuitive new interface designed for pro musicians, a ton of inspiring new plug-ins and sounds, and more powerful tools that keep the creative process flowing.
Language: English, Spanish, Chinese, German, French, Japanese


What's New in Version 10.0.2 - Aug 20, 2013
This update improves overall stability and performance issues including:


Undo commands work as expected after Flex Pitch editing
The Vintage Electric Piano plug-in now performs correctly at all sample rates
The Capture Last Take key command no longer erases a MIDI recording
Double-clicking on a Drummer region now opens or closes the editor
Addresses a graphic issue where the Piano Roll Editor could display an empty window


Changes
This update improves overall stability and performance issues including:


Fixes an issue that could cause content downloading to stall
24-bit audio files are no longer converted to 16-bit when exporting projects to AAF
Improves stability when switching between audio editors while Flex Pitch is enabled
Track Stacks that contain both software instrument and audio tracks will no longer * be inadvertently flattened by loading a Patch
Tuner is now available when selecting a Track Stack containing audio tracks
Addresses graphic and selection behavior issues in the Score Editor


Minimum System Requirements
4GB of RAM
Display with 1280-by-768 resolution or higher
OS X v10.8.4 or later
Requires 64-bit Audio Units plug-ins
Minimum 5GB of disk space. 35GB of optional content available via in-app download.

Requirements: OS X 10.8.4 or later, 64-bit processor 



Installation Instructions: 
------------------
Open "Logic Pro X 10.0.2.dmg"
Drag/Copy "Logic Pro X.app" to your "Applications" folder.
Thats it, you now have a fully functional copy of Logic Pro X.


When you open Logic Pro X for the first time. It will automatically start to download some components, don't worry this is normal behavior.


Important Note: 
------------------
Don't update Logic Pro X as updating it might cause a problem. You have been warned.


Enjoy
